&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=&#34;text-align:center;&#34;&gt;
Patients in interfacility transport missions had a significantly higher median (range) NACA Score 4 (2-5) compared with 3 (1-7), needed significantly more medical interventions, were significantly younger (59.6 ± 16 vs 65 ± 21 years), and were significantly more often male (73% vs 60.5%).
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
